      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For your \"universal guide\" to professional etiquette, consider including sections on:\n\n- Greetings and introductions, with a focus on addressing individuals with proper titles and surnames in cultures where this is customary, but also adapting to more informal greetings in Western societies.\n- Table manners, including proper use of utensils, napkin etiquette, and mealtime conversation topics that are universally considered polite.\n- Business attire and grooming standards, with a focus on dressing for the local climate and cultural norms, but also providing guidelines for more formal events.\n- Communication styles, including verbal and non-verbal cues, such as body language and tone of voice, that are universally considered professional and sophisticated.\n- Gift-giving and reciprocity, with guidelines on selecting and presenting gifts that are appropriate for different cultures and occasions.\n- Conflict resolution and diplomacy, with strategies for navigating difficult conversations and maintaining professional relationships in a global setting.",
